Welcome to the HOME OF THE HORNETS online 2019-2020. ​Milne-Kelvin Grove District 91 serves the residents of Lockport, Illinois with two schools: Milne Grove Elementary School (K-3) and Kelvin Grove Middle School (4-8). 





















 April 17, 2020 Update
 
Dear District 91 Families,

I hope this update finds you and your family doing well. Throughout the academic year, we examine how students are progressing as they move through the curriculum; this information helps our teachers make instructional decisions to meet the needs of students. Our teachers are committed to monitoring student progress even though daily instruction has moved outside of the walls of our classrooms. After our initial two weeks of remote learning, it appears that both staff and students are finding their comfort zone in this new method of instructional delivery and student engagement continues to be strong. 

With this information in mind and the Governor’s announcement today that we will continue remote learning through the end of the school year, we have updated our remote learning plan to include two additional components. The first is the addition of essential learning standards that will introduce new concepts and learning to students through a blended model of reviewing prior learning and moving forward with the introduction of additional curricular standards. This will allow us to provide essential skills and knowledge students require for the next grade level. The state recommendations for engagement and work established in the plan will remain the same. The second component to be included is enrichment activities for students. These activities will be beyond the minimum recommended instructional tasks, and are optional for all students. Students who would like to work on additional enrichment activities will find them in our Milne Grove Grade Level Classrooms and Kelvin Grove Cyber Library.

As we move forward, we will continue to review the remote learning plan and will make updates as needed. We will also continue to develop our on-site learning transition plan for the 2020-2021 school year. Parents can expect to receive communication from the building principals regarding our plans for the end of year events. These celebrations remain crucial to our school culture and sense of community. Even though they may not occur on the originally scheduled day or in the originally planned way, we are committed to honoring these important milestones.

Please remember that we are here to assist our families. If you are looking for resources, please see our district webpage for helpful information and links. If you have additional specific needs and you are not sure where to go for answers, please feel free to contact any of the District 91 administrative team. We are happy to assist you in finding information and answering your questions during remote learning. 

I hope to see all of our students back in our school buildings in the near future!

Sincerely

Donna Gray
Superintendent













